{
  "stem": "26140.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we knew that the sooner we go, the better, because when they move people in 1944-- at the end of 1944, winter, I seen in Buchenwald, they brought transport people frozen to death in the cattle wagons.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So when I went in summertime, I thought I did the best choice to move then.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because I could still avoid it if I wanted to, to ask to stay at Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I didn't, because I knew the end will be worse than that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had a commando where we had also Jews, Jewish people, which were sent to-- to work.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were working as brick layers and so on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were some Jews, which were selected to do the work.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When they were exhausted and died, they were sent to-- to be burned in crematorium.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But some of the Jews were working in our command.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, the Jewish people were rather worse than the other people, because the Polish people, if they had family, they had a chance to get a packet of food or whatever.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jewish people had no chance to get from nowhere.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's why I was always sorry for them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If I could sometimes give them a scrap, which I could afford to give, I give.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But otherwise, they were, in my opinion, worse than anybody else, because they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By cattle-- by train, we were moved to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we knew this won't be for long.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I know Buchenwald was bombed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One-- one day American Air Force came and bombed all the surrounding workplaces of Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I often thought, why didn't they do that in Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Send Air Force and bomb all the bunkers which were-- and crematoria, which were outside Auschwitz?",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
